VMusic festival
p3
sVnews
p4
VFor four years now, the residents of Coimbatore have had something to look forward to in the first fortnight of September. That is when the stars in the world of music come calling, to participate in the festival held by Rajalakshmi Fine Arts.  The v\u000aenue is Nani Palkhivala Hall, Mani Higher Secondary School. A food court and a CD stall will be added attractions.This year, the curtain goes up with the vocal recital of N. Vijaysiva. (6-9 p.m.) The artistes performing in the subsequent days are Bombay Jayashree Ramnath, P. Unnikrishnan, Gayatri Girish, T.M.Krishna  Sanjay Subrahmanyan, Sankari Krishnan, Akkarai Sisters Subhalakshmi and Swarnalatha (violin duet), Nithyasree Mahadevan, O.S.Arun (Bhajans), S. Sowmya,  Sikkil Gurucharan,  Malladi Brothers, Neyveli Santhanagopalan, Aruna Sairam  and Sudha Raghunathan.Junior musicians will perform in the 3-4.30 p.m. slot. Jaya Sreenivasan will present a musical discourse on &#8216;Thiruveni Ramayanam&#8217; (Ayodhya Kandam) from September 5 to 11, 4.30 p.m. to 5.45 p.m. From September 12 to 14, she will speak on &#8216;Krishna Thoodhu,&#8217; Mahabharatam).On the agenda is a series of lecture-demonstrations (10 a.m.-1 p.m.). On September 2, Jeyalaxmi will present a lecture-demonstration on &#8216;Rare  compositions of Muthaiah Bhagavatar,&#8217; her grandfather. On September 9, B.M.Sundaram will present  &#8216;Rare and  Compositions of Thanjavur Quartet.&#8217; On the concluding day (September 16), musicologist V.V.Srivatsa will speak on the &#8216;72 Mela Raga Compositions of Muthuswami Dikshitar.&#8217;For more details, call 0422-2231824, 98946-10043 or 98946-10005.
